President Biden has announced his intent to appoint several individuals as members to the Advisory Committee for Trade Policy and Negotiations. The committee provides policy advice to the United States Trade Representative on matters related to trade policy. The appointees have expertise in various areas, including manufacturing, environmental conservation, labor, and small business. Some of the notable appointees include Revathi Advaithi, the CEO of Flex, Manish Bapna, the President and CEO of the Natural Resources Defense Council, and Thomas M. Conway, the International President of the United Steelworkers union. Other appointees include individuals with experience in academia, law, and business.